28/11/2002
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- Yugoslav President Vojislav Kostunica and Albanian Foreign Minister Ilir Meta issued a statement after their meeting on Wednesday (27 November) pledging to continue to develop bilateral relations. 
They promised to respect their common border, human rights and minority rights, and said co-operation between Belgrade and Tirana would strengthen stability in the entire region.Meta said his country supports efforts to normalise the situation in Kosovo and to ensure peaceful co-existence. 
They also discussed efforts to bolster their respective bids for EU and NATO integration. 
In all, Meta signed 14 accords during his two-day stop in Belgrade. 
(AFP, ATA, Albanian News, Tanjug - 27/11/02)
